{
  "version": 2,
  "name": "ConcentricTunnel",
  "description": "Concentric polygon rings expanding outward from the centre — fully decomposed onto the curated atom library. The polyline-construction pattern is now visible as graph nodes (TouchDesigner Pattern → Math → Function → Merge shape) rather than sealed inside `node.polygon_shape` and `node.concentric_outlines` (both deleted in this pass).\n\nPer-frame outline construction:\n  mux_final_n_sides → generate_range(0, 2π, active_count=N, end_inclusive=false) → cos / sin via `array_math` → pack_curve_xy → outline[64]\n  mux_final_n_sides → consecutive_edges(closed=true) → edges[64]\n\nThe edge topology uses `EdgePair::SENTINEL` for the inactive tail (slots N..64), so a triangle drawn from a 64-slot buffer doesn't smear lines through 61 padding vertices. `pack_curve_xy.scale = 4.0` cancels the atom's internal `PROJ_SCALE = 0.25` Lissajous-screen-fit factor so the polygon's final radius matches `size = 1.0` directly (legacy parity).\n\nPer-frame ring stack:\n  i_array = generate_range(0, K-1, K=16, end_inclusive=true) → [0, 1, …, 15]\n  frac_exp = expansion − floor(expansion)\n  frac_offset = frac_exp × ring_spacing\n  scales = i_array × ring_spacing + frac_offset → [(frac_exp + i) × ring_spacing]\n  array_replicate_polyline_rings(outline, edges, scales) → outline[1024], edges[1024]\n  render_lines\n\nThe trigger-mode scaffolding (Shape / Spawn / Both via `clip_trigger_index` + `mux_cycle_sides` + `mux_final_n_sides` + `mode_*_enable` + `shape_active` / `spawn_active`) is unchanged from the previous bundled version — it was already in the graph, and it stays. Mux option tables (n-side choices, beat-rate choices, cycle sequence, mode gates) live as inline `in_N` params on the mux nodes themselves, not as a constellation of `node.value` constants wired in — the future node UI surfaces those inline values on the node body. The replicator atom inherits the sentinel-preserving edge propagation contract from the deleted `concentric_outlines` bundle: inactive input edges stay inactive in every output ring.",
